This sign has two distinct scripts. The first is actually made for the stone, bold, proud and golden. The second is placed below, in letters you must lean forward to see. A small X is written below that, it appears to be a duergar mark. 

-Written in gold script on an indestructable stone-
Be warned my friends! The duke of Brosna, in cooperation with the cities of Nordock, has made excellant preparations for travel and trade to this isle. It may be unforgiving to all but seasoned adventurers. I, Galdor, in grave mind and with the aid of all the forces of good, have opened this isle to travel and trade, once again, after over 200 years of isolation. Most can travel to the small city of Hebdezi if you stay to the roads. The forces of law shall keep this road open to those of good.

Lord Galdor, protector and watcher of Benzor.



-written later,  in indestructable but confident small black script below-
The way is open to those of our people. With bribe and challenge, the way is open for the deep. Beware the human city of Hebdezi, most have been bought, but the weak townsfolk cannot be appeased with gold. The merchants are with Mulrok, they shall barter with our kin. Lord Galdors plans have been circumvented (here lies a small pictograph profanity to dragons), he is vengeful but cannot negotiate. Go silent, go invisible, go swift in the city of Hebdezi.

I, Jarketh Thavin, librarian of Tetra, keeper of the tomes of the Ilythiiri of Nordock. Seeker of Vhaerun, uncaring of the dark maiden and faithful servant of the Queen. He who is always and never, have inscribed these lines for knowledge and glory.

-and below that, written in dark dwarven but indestructible-

X
